ding on the 28th floor of Hsinchu City \u2019 s \u201cSky Tree \u201d on the 26th, resulting in the deaths of two firemen, Li Yongzhen and Zhou Lixin. Today (28th) Hsinchu City Fire Department...\nCan't you watch it from your own family?\n\"Little Mermaid\" director points to Disney's problems\nDisney has been the first brand of American animation, bringing many beautiful memories to children around the world, including the early years of \"Snow White\", \"101 loyal dogs\", and what has been described as \"the Renaissance\".\nMay Tian Xin said! Donate billions of dollars to Taiwan Kaohsiung, Hualien, Yilan\nIn May, Ahsin \u2019 s words, \u201cWe Chinese, come to Beijing to eat roast duck, \u201d set off a rift between netizens on both sides of the Taiwan Strait, and was later poached to donate 9 million yuan (about 40.5 million NT dollars).\nHuang Hao Ping shares the first step in fraud prevention\nFraud news layer is endless, accidentally fell into the trap of bad people, \"Social Now What\" invited artist Huang Hao Ping as a guest host, the first video was invited to the Bureau of Criminal Affairs Prevention Division...\n\"China has no market\" by acid, can not earn RMB Yang Xiuhui counterattack\nRecently, many artists have taken the initiative to express their support for mainland reunification of Taiwan, and Yang Xiuhui is shouting \"I am Taiwanese\", which has won a lot of praise from Taiwanese netizens, but there are also many people who question her in mainland China.\nKorea 's first beautiful woman married for 17 years! Certified \"love and marriage are not the same\"\nSouth Korea 's first beauty Kim Hee-sun' s latest suspense psychological drama \"We, Home\", partner Bawant film after Lee Hui-ying, about Kim Hee-sun 's famous psychologist \"Lu Ying-yuan\" is threatened by mysterious people,...\nProduct recommendation\nudn Forum","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2024-0014.json.gz:9277","uncompressed_offset":801436266,"url":"udn.com/news/story/123693/7994260","warc_date":"2024-05-28T12:30:25.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752>","warc_url":"https://udn.com/news/story/123693/7994260"},"created":"2024-05-28T13:14:41.000Z","lang":"eng"},"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":{"id":"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498","text":"Advertisment\n\nHow Disney's The Little Mermaid Live-Action Remake Is Changing the Narrative\n\nDisney's live-action remake of The Little Mermaid has made a significant impact by surpassing the original's box office earnings, offering representation to young girls of color, and standing firm against racist backlash.\n\nBNN Correspondents\nNew Update\n\nIn a world where representation matters more than ever, Disney's live-action remake of The Little Mermaid has set a new benchmark. The film, which grossed over $550 million in global ticket sales, has surpassed the original's box office earnings, making a significant financial and cultural impact. Beyond merely being entertaining, the film has become a beacon of hope for young girls of color, seeing themselves represented in a fantasy world for the first time.\n\nAdvertisment\n\nReimagining Inclusion in Fantasy\n\nThe casting of Halle Bailey as Ariel sparked controversy even before filming began. Detractors used AI to alter her features to resemble a white woman, reflecting a narrow view of what a mermaid, or a princess, should look like. Despite the racist backlash, Disney stood firm, challenging the status quo and reimagining inclusion in fantasy. The film's success underscores the necessity of diversity in storytelling, proving that audiences are hungry for fresh perspectives and narratives that resonate with their own experiences.\n\nStanding Firm Against Racism\n\nAdvertisment\n\nThe release of the first teaser at D23 Expo was met with enthusiasm and anticipation. The beautiful shots of Halle Bailey's Ariel in the ocean, accompanied by the iconic Part of Your World, were a powerful assertion of Disney's commitment to diversity. The film, directed by Rob Marshall and released in May 2023, also features Jonah Hauer-King as Prince Eric, Melissa McCarthy as Ursula, Awkwafina as Scuttle, Jacob Tremblay as Flounder, Javier Bardem as King Triton, Daveed Diggs as Sebastian, and Noma Dumezweni in an undisclosed role. Each casting choice was a testament to the company's determination to stand against racist attacks and uphold the importance of representation.\n\nAttending to Details for Authentic Representation\n\nWith its Reimagine Tomorrow initiative, Disney is leading the way in promoting diversity and inclusion across its productions. By paying meticulous attention to details, the company ensures authentic and inclusive representation both on-screen and off-screen. The success of The Little Mermaid underlines the significance of these efforts, and the film serves as a potent reminder that stories have the power to inspire change.\n\nIn conclusion, the journey of The Little Mermaid offers valuable lessons for leadership and the power of storytelling. It highlights the importance of standing firm against critics, especially in the face of racism. It also emphasizes the necessity to reimagine inclusion in fantasy and the significance of paying attention to details for authentic representation. These lessons are not just applicable to film-making, but are relevant in all fields where leaders have the opportunity to challenge hate and inspire change through their work.\n\nAdvertisment\nAdvertisment","url":"https://bnnbreaking.com/arts/how-disneys-the-little-mermaid-live-action-remake-is-changing-the-narrative/"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1018","request_id":"1018","narrative_id":"1018"},"responses":[{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Disney's live-action remakes of animated classics are largely driven by the desire to reduce financial risk while capitalizing on audience nostalgia, as these films reimagine beloved stories that have already proven successful in the past."},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"As the first major brand in American animation, Disney has created a legacy of cherished memories for audiences worldwide, from early classics like 'Snow White' and '101 Dalmatians' to the 'Renaissance' era with hits such as 'Beauty and the Beast' and 'Aladdin.'"},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Nostalgia plays a pivotal role in Disney's strategy, as these remakes tap into the emotional connections audiences have with the original films, ensuring a built-in fan base and a higher likelihood of box office success."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"The live-action remake of 'The Little Mermaid' exemplifies Disney's efforts to adapt timeless stories for modern audiences by offering representation to young girls of color and addressing contemporary social issues."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"By casting Halle Bailey as Ariel, Disney challenged traditional norms in fantasy storytelling, demonstrating a commitment to diversity and inclusion that resonates with today's audiences."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"This approach aligns with Disney's broader 'Reimagine Tomorrow' initiative, which aims to promote diversity and authentic representation both on-screen and behind the scenes."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"The success of 'The Little Mermaid' remake underscores the importance of diverse storytelling and the transformative power of inclusive narratives in inspiring societal change."},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"However, some critics argue that certain live-action remakes, such as 'The Little Mermaid,' have neglected core elements of the original stories, such as the father-daughter relationship, while also featuring less expressive character designs compared to the animated versions."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"The casting of Halle Bailey as Ariel sparked significant public debate, with some detractors resorting to using AI to alter her features to resemble a white woman, highlighting ongoing societal tensions around representation in media."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"Despite the backlash, the release of the first teaser for 'The Little Mermaid' at the D23 Expo was met with widespread enthusiasm and anticipation, showcasing the strong emotional connection audiences have with Disney's classic stories."},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Disney's live-action remakes have often faced criticism for prioritizing political correctness and modern messaging over the depth of story and character development, leading to mixed audience reception."},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Audience ratings for Disney's live-action adaptations have frequently been less favorable compared to the original animated films, reflecting the challenges of meeting high expectations tied to nostalgia."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"The live-action version of 'The Little Mermaid' features a diverse cast, including Halle Bailey, Jonah Hauer-King, Melissa McCarthy, Awkwafina, Jacob Tremblay, Javier Bardem, Daveed Diggs, and Noma Dumezweni, showcasing Disney's commitment to inclusivity."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"Financially, 'The Little Mermaid' live-action remake outperformed the original animated film, grossing over $550 million globally, demonstrating the commercial viability of these adaptations."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"The cultural impact of 'The Little Mermaid' remake extends beyond its box office success, as it has become a symbol of representation and resilience against racist backlash."},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Disney's strategy of producing live-action remakes reflects a calculated effort to balance authenticity with relevance, ensuring that these stories resonate with both nostalgic fans and new generations."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Disney's live-action remakes of animated classics are largely driven by the desire to reduce financial risk while capitalizing on audience nostalgia, as these films reimagine beloved stories that have already proven successful in the past."},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"As the first major brand in American animation, Disney has created a legacy of cherished memories for audiences worldwide, from early classics like 'Snow White' and '101 Dalmatians' to the 'Renaissance' era with hits such as 'Beauty and the Beast' and 'Aladdin.'"},{"citations":{"04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752_801436266":100.0},"text":"Nostalgia plays a pivotal role in Disney's strategy, as these remakes tap into the emotional connections audiences have with the original films, ensuring a built-in fan base and a higher likelihood of box office success."},{"citations":{"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":100.0},"text":"The live-action remake of 'The Little Mermaid' exemplifies Disney