ssed_offset":801436266,"url":"udn.com/news/story/123693/7994260","warc_date":"2024-05-28T12:30:25.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:04be02f4-bf63-4cf4-a520-2859d5be0752>","warc_url":"https://udn.com/news/story/123693/7994260"},"created":"2024-05-28T13:14:41.000Z","lang":"eng"},"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498":{"id":"84e42260-399c-4d7b-8ea7-6f4f8bd47c33_545966498","text":"Advertisment\n\nHow Disney's The Little Mermaid Live-Action Remake Is Changing the Narrative\n\nDisney's live-action remake of The Little Mermaid has made a significant impact by surpassing the original's box office earnings, offering representation to young girls of color, and standing firm against racist backlash.\n\nBNN Correspondents\nNew Update\n\nIn a world where representation matters more than ever, Disney's live-action remake of The Little Mermaid has set a new benchmark. The film, which grossed over $550 million in global ticket sales, has surpassed the original's box office earnings, making a significant financial and cultural impact. Beyond merely being entertaining, the film has become a beacon of hope for young girls of color, seeing themselves represented in a fantasy world for the first time.\n\nAdvertisment\n\nReimagining Inclusion in Fantasy\n\nThe casting of Halle Bailey as Ariel sparked controversy even before filming began. Detractors used AI to alter her features to resemble a white woman, reflecting a narrow view of what a mermaid, or a princess, should look like. Despite the racist backlash, Disney stood firm, challenging the status quo and reimagining inclusion in fantasy. The film's success underscores the necessity of diversity in storytelling, proving that audiences are hungry for fresh perspectives and narratives that resonate with their own experiences.\n\nStanding Firm Against Racism\n\nAdvertisment\n\nThe release of the first teaser at D23 Expo was met with enthusiasm and anticipation. The beautiful shots of Halle Bailey's Ariel in the ocean, accompanied by the iconic Part of Your World, were a powerful assertion of Disney's commitment to diversity. The film, directed by Rob Marshall and released in May 2023, also features Jonah Hauer-King as Prince Eric, Melissa McCarthy as Ursula, Awkwafina as Scuttle, Jacob Tremblay as Flounder, Javier Bardem as King Triton, Daveed Diggs as Sebastian, and Noma Dumezweni in an undisclosed role. Each casting choice was a testament to the company's determination to stand against racist attacks and uphold the importance of representation.\n\nAttending to Details for Authentic Representation\n\nWith its Reimagine Tomorrow initiative, Disney is leading the way in promoting diversity and inclusion across its productions. By paying meticulous attention to details, the company ensures authentic and inclusive representation both on-screen and off-screen. The success of The Little Mermaid underlines the significance of these efforts, and the film serves as a potent reminder that stories have the power to inspire change.\n\nIn conclusion, the journey of The Little Mermaid offers valuable lessons for leadership and the power of storytelling. It highlights the importance of standing firm against critics, especially in the face of racism. It also emphasizes the necessity to reimagine inclusion in fantasy and the significance of paying attention to details for authentic representation. These lessons are not just applicable to film-making, but are relevant in all fields where leaders have the opportunity to challenge hate and inspire change through their work.\n\nAdvertisment\nAdvertisment","url":"https://bnnbreaking.com/arts/how-disneys-the-little-mermaid-live-action-remake-is-changing-the-narrative/"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1019","request_id":"1019","narrative_id":"1019"},"responses":[{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi, a centuries-old Chinese martial art also known as shadow boxing, combines physical training, self-defense, and meditation to promote overall well-being."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The practice emphasizes slow, flowing movements that harmonize body and mind, fostering relaxation and psychological comfort."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi exercises gently stimulate and stretch muscles, tendons, joints, and bones, making it particularly suitable for older adults seeking low-impact physical activity."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The upright posture maintained during Tai Chi sessions helps stretch the spine and relieve pressure on intervertebral discs, contributing to better spinal health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Additionally, Tai Chi positively influences the nervous system through its gentle back posture, which may enhance overall physical stability."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Scientific studies have shown that Tai Chi is effective in reducing the risk of falls among older adults by improving balance and coordination."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The slow, deliberate movements of Tai Chi enhance proprioception, or the body\u2019s ability to sense its position in space, which is crucial for preventing falls."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi also offers additional health benefits, such as alleviating symptoms of degenerative arthritis, including knee stiffness, pain, and swelling."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"For individuals with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), Tai Chi has been shown to improve lung function and respiratory health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Patients with Parkinson\u2019s disease may experience improved balance and mobility through regular Tai Chi practice, enhancing their quality of life."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi has also been found to enhance cognitive functioning, making it a valuable activity for individuals with dementia."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The meditative aspect of Tai Chi not only promotes mental alertness but also helps reduce stress, which can indirectly support physical stability and fall prevention."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Given its gentle nature and wide-ranging benefits, Tai Chi is an accessible and effective option for older adults aiming to stay active and reduce their risk of falls."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi, a centuries-old Chinese martial art also known as shadow boxing, combines physical training, self-defense, and meditation to promote overall well-being."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The practice emphasizes slow, flowing movements that harmonize body and mind, fostering relaxation and psychological comfort."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi exercises gently stimulate and stretch muscles, tendons, joints, and bones, making it particularly suitable for older adults seeking low-impact physical activity."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The upright posture maintained during Tai Chi sessions helps stretch the spine and relieve pressure on intervertebral discs, contributing to better spinal health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Additionally, Tai Chi positively influences the nervous system through its gentle back posture, which may enhance overall physical stability."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Scientific studies have shown that Tai Chi is effective in reducing the risk of falls among older adults by improving balance and coordination."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The slow, deliberate movements of Tai Chi enhance proprioception, or the body\u2019s ability to sense its position in space, which is crucial for preventing falls."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi also offers additional health benefits, such as alleviating symptoms of degenerative arthritis, including knee stiffness, pain, and swelling."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"For individuals with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), Tai Chi has been shown to improve lung function and respiratory health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Patients with Parkinson\u2019s disease may experience improved balance and mobility through regular Tai Chi practice, enhancing their quality of life."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi has also been found to enhance cognitive functioning, making it a valuable activity for individuals with dementia."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The meditative aspect of Tai Chi not only promotes mental alertness but also helps reduce stress, which can indirectly support physical stability and fall prevention."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Given its gentle nature and wide-ranging benefits, Tai Chi is an accessible and effective option for older adults aiming to stay active and reduce their risk of falls."}],"references":["2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624"],"documents":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":{"id":"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624","text":"Learn about the sport of Tai Chi\nThe German health centre says Tai Chi is a centuries-old Chinese martial art, also known as shadow boxing.\nIt combines physical training, self-defense and meditation.\nThe focus of Tai Chi is on body tightening, mental alertness and breathing, the center explained, noting that motor training consists of a series of traditional Chinese physical exercises that flow smoothly with each other in order to achieve harmony between body and soul.\nMuscle and Joint Stimulation\nIn this way all the muscles, tendons, joints and bones are stimulated and stretched in a gentle way.\nThe upright position of the back during exercise creates a stretching effect in the spine, relieving pressure on the intervertebral discs.\nThe nervous system is also positively affected by the gentle posture of the back.\nStudies have suggested that tai chi reduces the risk of falls in older adults thanks to its ability to improve their balance.\nThe sport also has a positive effect on degenerative arthritis, the symptoms of which are knee stiffness, pain and swelling.\nImprove lung function\nTai chi is also beneficial for chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) as it improves lung function.\nIt is also useful for patients with Parkinson \u2019 s, which affects the nervous system and its symptoms are disorders of movement, tremor of the hands, stiffness and instability of the body position, where sports contribute to improving balance and mobility.\nIn addition, tai chi improves the cognitive functioning of the brain, making it also useful for dementia patients.\nOn the other hand, slow flowing movements have a relaxing and meditative effect, helping to feel relaxed, calm and psychologically comfortable.\nSource: German","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2024-0010.json.gz:18937","uncompressed_offset":437053624,"url":"www.aljazeera.net/health/2024/4/16/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%81-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%8A","warc_date":"2024-04-16T18:28:32.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237>","warc_url":"https://www.aljazeera.net/health/2024/4/16/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%81-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%8A?traffic_source=rss"},"created":"2024-04-16T18:55:44.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1020","request_id":"1020","narrative_id":"1020"},"responses":[{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi, also known as shadow boxing, is a centuries-old Chinese martial art that integrates physical training, self-defense techniques, and meditation practices."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The practice emphasizes smooth, flowing movements that aim to harmonize the body and mind, focusing on body tightening, mental alertness, and controlled breathing."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi exercises are designed to gently stimulate and stretch muscles, tendons, joints, and bones, making it a low-impact activity suitable for individuals of all ages."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The slow and deliberate movements of Tai Chi not only promote physical flexibility but also have a calming and meditative effect, fostering psychological comfort and relaxation."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"One of the key physical benefits of Tai Chi is its ability to stretch the spine through upright posture, which can relieve pressure on the intervertebral discs and support overall spinal health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Additionally, the gentle postures practiced in Tai Chi positively influence the nervous system, contributing to improved physical and mental well-being."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Scientific studies have shown that Tai Chi is effective in reducing the risk of falls among older adults by enhancing balance and coordination."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The practice of Tai Chi has also been found to alleviate symptoms of degenerative arthritis, such as knee stiffness, pain, and swelling, making it a valuable exercise for joint health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"For individuals with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), Tai Chi has been shown to improve lung function and respiratory health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi is particularly beneficial for patients with Parkinson\u2019s disease, as it helps improve balance and mobility, which are often compromised by the condition."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Moreover, Tai Chi has been linked to enhanced cognitive functioning, making it a supportive activity for individuals with dementia or other cognitive impairments."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi, also known as shadow boxing, is a centuries-old Chinese martial art that integrates physical training, self-defense techniques, and meditation practices."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The practice emphasizes smooth, flowing movements that aim to harmonize the body and mind, focusing on body tightening, mental alertness, and controlled breathing."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi exercises are designed to gently stimulate and stretch muscles, tendons, joints, and bones, making it a low-impact activity suitable for individuals of all ages."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The slow and deliberate movements of Tai Chi not only promote physical flexibility but also have a calming and meditative effect, fostering psychological comfort and relaxation."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"One of the key physical benefits of Tai Chi is its ability to stretch the spine through upright posture, which can relieve pressure on the intervertebral discs and support overall spinal health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Additionally, the gentle postures practiced in Tai Chi positively influence the nervous system, contributing to improved physical and mental well-being."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Scientific studies have shown that Tai Chi is effective in reducing the risk of falls among older adults by enhancing balance and coordination."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"The practice of Tai Chi has also been found to alleviate symptoms of degenerative arthritis, such as knee stiffness, pain, and swelling, making it a valuable exercise for joint health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"For individuals with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), Tai Chi has been shown to improve lung function and respiratory health."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Tai Chi is particularly beneficial for patients with Parkinson\u2019s disease, as it helps improve balance and mobility, which are often compromised by the condition."},{"citations":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":100.0},"text":"Moreover, Tai Chi has been linked to enhanced cognitive functioning, making it a supportive activity for individuals with dementia or other cognitive impairments."}],"references":["2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624"],"documents":{"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624":{"id":"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624","text":"Learn about the sport of Tai Chi\nThe German health centre says Tai Chi is a centuries-old Chinese martial art, also known as shadow boxing.\nIt combines physical training, self-defense and meditation.\nThe focus of Tai Chi is on body tightening, mental alertn