 economies are long-term drivers of single-aisle aircraft demand."},{"citations":{"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685":100.0},"text":"In the short term, the rebound in domestic and regional air travel is prompting airlines to place orders for new, fuel-efficient single-aisle models."},{"citations":{"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685":100.0},"text":"Narrow-body aircraft are the largest segment in the single-aisle market, favored for their versatility and cost-efficiency on both domestic and international routes."},{"citations":{"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685":100.0},"text":"Fleet modernization in mature markets like North America and Europe is driving demand for state-of-the-art single-aisle aircraft to enhance efficiency and passenger comfort."},{"citations":{"65a6d821-4ded-4ba5-874a-2aa5ee48ba5e_72581204":100.0},"text":"The Airbus A320neo and Boeing 737 Max 8 are expected to dominate the single-aisle jet market, collectively representing 50% of deliveries."},{"citations":{"65a6d821-4ded-4ba5-874a-2aa5ee48ba5e_72581204":100.0},"text":"Airbus and Boeing are planning to introduce a new generation of single-aisle aircraft in the early to mid-2030s to maintain their competitive edge."},{"citations":{"65a6d821-4ded-4ba5-874a-2aa5ee48ba5e_72581204":100.0},"text":"In the dual-aisle market, the Boeing 787 and Airbus A350 are projected to dominate, capturing a significant share of the $1.1 trillion market."},{"citations":{"9973d6d5-a9dc-411f-a89d-969510946c96_466373894":100.0},"text":"Airbus, the largest aircraft manufacturer globally, operates industrial facilities in Germany, France, and the Netherlands, and produces models like the A380, the world's largest aircraft."},{"citations":{"9973d6d5-a9dc-411f-a89d-969510946c96_466373894":100.0},"text":"Boeing, headquartered in Chicago, is renowned for its commercial and military aircraft, as well as its ventures in space exploration."},{"citations":{"9973d6d5-a9dc-411f-a89d-969510946c96_