etween China and Africa has played a pivotal role in poverty reduction, fostering economic growth and development."},{"citations":{"fe0a09f8-0d9d-405b-a939-27fdd4642f3a_813234696":100.0},"text":"The China-Africa Youth Innovation and Entrepreneurship Forum promotes collaboration between young entrepreneurs from both regions, fostering innovation and mutual growth."},{"citations":{"fe0a09f8-0d9d-405b-a939-27fdd4642f3a_813234696":100.0},"text":"The China-Africa Women's Forum has launched initiatives such as the '10 square meters mushroom farm' in South Africa to empower women and enhance cooperation."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"a948934f-cc3e-4b6b-ba17-7748e34ef2c6_397268782":100.0},"text":"Foreign direct investment (FDI) flows into Africa experienced a significant decline of 16 percent in 2020, dropping to $40 billion from $47 billion in 2019, as reported by the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD)."},{"citations":{"a948934f-cc3e-4b6b-ba17-7748e34ef2c6_397268782":100.0},"text":"Despite this downturn, FDI inflows into Africa were projected to grow modestly by 5 percent in 2021, reflecting cautious optimism about the region's investment climate."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":100.0},"text":"By 2022, foreign direct investment in Africa rebounded to $45 billion, returning to pre-pandemic levels and signaling renewed confidence among global investors."},{"citations":{"a948934f-cc3e-4b6b-ba17-7748e34ef2c6_397268782":100.0},"text":"Africa's demographic and economic potential is immense, with the continent currently home to 17 percent of the global population, a figure expected to rise to 26 percent by 2050, amounting to 2.53 billion people."},{"citations":{"a948934f-cc3e-4b6b-ba17-7748e34ef2c6_397268782":100.0},"text":"By mid-century, Africa is projected to have a combined consumer and business spending capacity of $16.12 trillion, underscoring its growing economic significance."},{"citations":{"a948934f-cc3e-4b6b-ba17-