ases has been increasingly recognized in contemporary research."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677":100.0},"text":"Jammu and Kashmir has historically been a significant hub for the Indian system of medicine, boasting a rich tradition of Ayurvedic hospitals and pharmacies."},{"citations":{"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677":100.0},"text":"To strengthen secondary healthcare, five 50-bedded Integrated AYUSH Hospitals have been approved in the districts of Kulgam, Kathua, Kupwara, Kishtwar, and Samba under the National AYUSH Mission."},{"citations":{"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677":100.0},"text":"In an effort to promote medical tourism, six specialized AYUSH wellness centers have been approved at tourist locations in Jammu and Kashmir, with three already operational."},{"citations":{"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677":100.0},"text":"The establishment of the Ayurvedic Medical College and Hospital in Akhnoor and the Unani Medical College and Hospital in Ganderbal marks a significant enhancement in healthcare infrastructure in Jammu and Kashmir."},{"citations":{"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677":100.0},"text":"The Ministry of AYUSH, in collaboration with the Jammu and Kashmir administration, is working under the vision of 'One Earth, One Health' to integrate ancient Indian systems of medicine into global healthcare frameworks."},{"citations":{"e2101fe3-e219-47c1-8300-449bef7dfe12_68754735":100.0},"text":"The Indian government has advocated for the inclusion of Ayurveda and related systems in the 11th revision of the World Health Organisation\u2019s International Classification of Diseases (ICD) as part of a supplementary chapter on traditional medicine conditions."},{"citations":{"e2101fe3-e219-47c1-8300-449bef7dfe12_68754735":100.0},"text":"Incorporating Ayurveda into the ICD-11 provides a standardized language for health professionals worldwide to share information effectively