rk created over 110 years ago, has been subjected to numerous acts of vandalism throughout its history."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"Among the most notable incidents, the statue was decapitated twice, marking a particularly severe form of damage to the artwork."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2003, the statue was targeted with explosives, which caused it to be knocked off its base, representing one of the most destructive attacks in its history."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2017, the statue was doused in red paint as part of a protest against whale hunting, highlighting its use as a platform for environmental activism."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"During the global protests following George Floyd's death in 2020, the words 'racist fish' were painted on the statue's base, linking the act of vandalism to broader discussions on racial justice."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"Most recently, in March 2023, the statue was defaced with the Russian flag painted on the stone it sits on, an act that drew immediate attention and prompted an investigation by authorities."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Russian flag incident was discovered early on a Thursday, and authorities began efforts to identify the perpetrator and understand the motivations behind the act."}],"references":["f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400"],"documents":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":{"id":"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400","text":"Russian Flag Painted on Copenhagen's Most Famous Landmark\n\nIt's the latest in a long line of attacks on Little Mermaid statue\nBy Rob Quinn, \u00a0Newser Staff\nPosted Mar 2, 2023 10:15 AM CST\n\nThe Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, one of Denmark's most famous landmarks, has been vandalized yet again, this time with the Russian flag. Authorities said Thursday that the white, blue, and red stripes of the Russian flag were painted on the stone the statue sits on, Reuters reports. Police said the vandalism was discovered early Thursday. \"We are of course launching an investigation to find out who did it and when and how it happened,\" a police spokesman said, per Jyllands-Posten.\n\nDenmark, like other European nations, has strongly criticized Russia's war against Ukraine. The small statue, a tribute to the Hans Christian Andersen fairy tale, sits off a waterfront promenade in the Danish capital. It has been vandalized many times since it was installed 110 years ago, AFP reports. It has been decapitated twice and was knocked off its base with explosives in 2003. In 2017, it was doused in red paint in a protest against whale hunting. In 2020, during worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base, though Andersen scholars said they weren't aware of any racist elements in the fairy tale. (Read more The Little Mermaid stories.)\n\nWe use cookies. By Clicking \"OK\" or any content on this site, you agree to allow cookies to be placed. Read more in our privacy policy.\nGet the news faster.\nTap to install our app.\nX\nInstall the Newser News app\nin two easy steps:\n1. Tap in your navigation bar.\n2. Tap to Add to Home Screen.\n\nX","url":"https://www.newser.com/story/332238/little-mermaid-statue-vandalized-with-russian-flag.html"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1044","request_id":"1044","narrative_id":"1044"},"responses":[{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, a cultural landmark and symbol of Denmark, has been subjected to numerous acts of vandalism over its 110-year history, reflecting its prominence and the diverse motivations behind these incidents."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"One of the most striking forms of vandalism occurred when the statue was decapitated on two separate occasions, underscoring the extreme measures taken by some individuals to deface this iconic artwork."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2003, the statue was targeted with explosives, resulting in it being knocked off its base, an act that demonstrated the lengths to which vandals would go to disrupt and damage this cultural symbol."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2017, the statue was doused in red paint as part of a protest against whale hunting, highlighting how the statue has been used as a platform for expressing environmental and ethical concerns."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"During the global protests following George Floyd's death in 2020, the words 'racist fish' were painted on the base of the statue, linking the act of vandalism to broader discussions about racism and social justice."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In March 2023, the statue was defaced with the Russian flag painted on the stone it sits on, an act that drew immediate attention and prompted an investigation by authorities to identify the perpetrator and understand the motivations behind it."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Russian flag incident was discovered early on a Thursday, and it spurred a swift response from law enforcement to determine the circumstances surrounding this act of vandalism."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, a cultural landmark and symbol of Denmark, has been subjected to numerous acts of vandalism over its 110-year history, reflecting its prominence and the diverse motivations behind these incidents."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"One of the most striking forms of vandalism occurred when the statue was decapitated on two separate occasions, underscoring the extreme measures taken by some individuals to deface this iconic artwork."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2003, the statue was targeted with explosives, resulting in it being knocked off its base, an act that demonstrated the lengths to which vandals would go to disrupt and damage this cultural symbol."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2017, the statue was doused in red paint as part of a protest against whale hunting, highlighting how the statue has been used as a platform for expressing environmental and ethical concerns."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"During the global protests following George Floyd's death in 2020, the words 'racist fish' were painted on the base of the statue, linking the act of vandalism to broader discussions about racism and social justice."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In March 2023, the statue was defaced with the Russian flag painted on the stone it sits on, an act that drew immediate attention and prompted an investigation by authorities to identify the perpetrator and understand the motivations behind it."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Russian flag incident was discovered early on a Thursday, and it spurred a swift response from law enforcement to determine the circumstances surrounding this act of vandalism."}],"references":["f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400"],"documents":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":{"id":"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400","text":"Russian Flag Painted on Copenhagen's Most Famous Landmark\n\nIt's the latest in a long line of attacks on Little Mermaid statue\nBy Rob Quinn, \u00a0Newser Staff\nPosted Mar 2, 2023 10:15 AM CST\n\nThe Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, one of Denmark's most famous landmarks, has been vandalized yet again, this time with the Russian flag. Authorities said Thursday that the white, blue, and red stripes of the Russian flag were painted on the stone the statue sits on, Reuters reports. Police said the vandalism was discovered early Thursday. \"We are of course launching an investigation to find out who did it and when and how it happened,\" a police spokesman said, per Jyllands-Posten.\n\nDenmark, like other European nations, has strongly criticized Russia's war against Ukraine. The small statue, a tribute to the Hans Christian Andersen fairy tale, sits off a waterfront promenade in the Danish capital. It has been vandalized many times since it was installed 110 years ago, AFP reports. It has been decapitated twice and was knocked off its base with explosives in 2003. In 2017, it was doused in red paint in a protest against whale hunting. In 2020, during worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base, though Andersen scholars said they weren't aware of any racist elements in the fairy tale. (Read more The Little Mermaid stories.)\n\nWe use cookies. By Clicking \"OK\" or any content on this site, you agree to allow cookies to be placed. Read more in our privacy policy.\nGet the news faster.\nTap to install our app.\nX\nInstall the Newser News app\nin two easy steps:\n1. Tap in your navigation bar.\n2. Tap to Add to Home Screen.\n\nX","url":"https://www.newser.com/story/332238/little-mermaid-statue-vandalized-with-russian-flag.html"}}}
