ndividuals painted the Russian flag on the stone base of the statue, prompting a police investigation into the act of vandalism."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Russian flag incident in 2023 was widely interpreted as a political statement, though the motives behind the act remain unclear."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"Over the years, the Little Mermaid statue has been decapitated twice, painted multiple times, and even subjected to explosive damage, underscoring its vulnerability as a public artwork."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"These repeated acts of vandalism reflect the statue\u2019s dual role as both a cherished cultural icon and a canvas for political and social expression."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, an iconic cultural landmark, has been subjected to repeated acts of vandalism since its installation in 1913."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"One of the most infamous incidents occurred in 1964 when the statue was decapitated, and the head was stolen, never to be recovered."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"In 1998, the statue was decapitated again by vandals, but this time the head was restored, allowing the statue to regain its original form."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"Explosives were used in 2003 to knock the statue off its base, marking one of the most destructive attacks in its history."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The explosion in 2003 caused significant damage to the statue, prompting extensive restoration efforts."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2017, the statue was doused in red paint as part of a protest against whale hunting, highlighting its use as a platform for political statements."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"During the global protests following the death of George Floyd in 2020, the statue was defaced with graffiti reading 'racist fish,' reflecting its role in broader social debates."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The same 2020 incident saw the words 'racist fish' painted on the statue\u2019s base, sparking discussions about its cultural symbolism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"In March 2023, unidentified individuals painted the Russian flag on the stone base of the statue, prompting a police investigation into the act of vandalism."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Russian flag incident in 2023 was widely interpreted as a political statement, though the motives behind the act remain unclear."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"Over the years, the Little Mermaid statue has been decapitated twice, painted multiple times, and even subjected to explosive damage, underscoring its vulnerability as a public artwork."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"These repeated acts of vandalism reflect the statue\u2019s dual role as both a cherished cultural icon and a canvas for political and social expression."}],"references":["4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268","f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400"],"documents":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":{"id":"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400","text":"Russian Flag Painted on Copenhagen's Most Famous Landmark\n\nIt's the latest in a long line of attacks on Little Mermaid statue\nBy Rob Quinn, \u00a0Newser Staff\nPosted Mar 2, 2023 10:15 AM CST\n\nThe Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, one of Denmark's most famous landmarks, has been vandalized yet again, this time with the Russian flag. Authorities said Thursday that the white, blue, and red stripes of the Russian flag were painted on the stone the statue sits on, Reuters reports. Police said the vandalism was discovered early Thursday. \"We are of course launching an investigation to find out who did it and when and how it happened,\" a police spokesman said, per Jyllands-Posten.\n\nDenmark, like other European nations, has strongly criticized Russia's war against Ukraine. The small statue, a tribute to the Hans Christian Andersen fairy tale, sits off a waterfront promenade in the Danish capital. It has been vandalized many times since it was installed 110 years ago, AFP reports. It has been decapitated twice and was knocked off its base with explosives in 2003. In 2017, it was doused in red paint in a protest against whale hunting. In 2020, during worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base, though Andersen scholars said they weren't aware of any racist elements in the fairy tale. (Read more The Little Mermaid stories.)\n\nWe use cookies. By Clicking \"OK\" or any content on this site, you agree to allow cookies to be placed. Read more in our privacy policy.\nGet the news faster.\nTap to install our app.\nX\nInstall the Newser News app\nin two easy steps:\n1. Tap in your navigation bar.\n2. Tap to Add to Home Screen.\n\nX","url":"https://www.newser.com/story/332238/little-mermaid-statue-vandalized-with-russian-flag.html"},"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":{"id":"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268","text":"Unknown people draw Russian flag on a statue of a mermaid in Copenhagen\nCOPENHAGEN (AFP) - The iconic Little Mermaid statue in the Danish capital Copenhagen was vandalized on Wednesday night as unidentified people painted the Russian flag on its base.\nAnnouncement\nAn AFP correspondent reported that the Russian flag was painted under unknown circumstances on the stone above which a statue of the Little Mermaid, inspired by the heroine of one of the stories of the writer Hans Christian Andersen, was installed.\nDanish police said they were launching an investigation into the incident, without giving any indication of the source of the move, which shows clear support for Russia amid the ongoing war in Ukraine.\nA Copenhagen police spokesman told AFP: \"We are investigating the area in order to find any evidence.\"\nA small number of tourists in the area took pictures of the statue in the port of Copenhagen, which was vandalized on Thursday morning.\nThe Little Mermaid statue on a largely unfrequented promenade has been targeted several times since it was installed in 1913.\nIn 1964, the head of the nymph was stolen for the first time without being recovered.\nIn 1998, a group of vandals cut off the head of the statue again, but it was later restored.\nThis monument was exposed to the explosion in 2003.\nThe statue, created by Danish sculptor Edvard Eriksen, has also been targeted several times with graffiti or graffiti, most recently in 2020 with the inscription \u201cracist fish \u201d.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0006.json.gz:38440","uncompressed_offset":592630268,"url":"www.france24.com/ar/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9/20230302-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%87%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%BA%D9%86","warc_date":"2023-03-03T12:29:55.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4>","warc_url":"https://www.france24.com/ar/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9/20230302-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%87%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%BA%D9%86"},"created":"2023-03-03T12:51:55.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1046","request_id":"1046","narrative_id":"1046"},"responses":[{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen has been a target of repeated intentional damages since its installation 110 years ago, with various incidents of vandalism, including decapitation, explosive damage, and painting or graffiti, which will be explored in this report."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"One of the most notable forms of vandalism the statue has suffered is decapitation, which has occurred twice, with the first incident happening in 1964, when the head of the Little Mermaid statue was stolen and never recovered."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The second decapitation incident occurred in 1998, when vandals cut off the head of the Little Mermaid statue again, but it was later restored, highlighting the ongoing struggle to protect the statue from intentional damage."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In addition to decapitation, the statue has also been damaged by explosives, with a notable incident occurring in 2003, when the Little Mermaid statue was knocked off its base using explosives, causing significant damage."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The explosive damage in 2003 was not an isolated incident, as the statue was also damaged by an explosion in the same year, further emphasizing the need for increased security measures to prevent such incidents."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue has also been targeted with painting and graffiti, with a recent incident occurring in March 2023, when the Russian flag was painted on the stone it sits on, prompting a police investigation."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2017, the statue was doused in red paint as part of a protest against whale hunting, demonstrating how the statue has become a focal point for various social and political movements."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The statue was also defaced with graffiti reading 'racist fish' in 2020, during worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, highlighting the complex and often controversial nature of the statue's symbolism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The incident of painting the Russian flag on the base of the Little Mermaid statue in 2023 was not an isolated event, as unidentified individuals had also painted the same flag on the base, prompting a police investigation and raising concerns about the statue's security."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The defacing of the Little Mermaid statue with graffiti reading 'racist fish' in 2020 was a significant incident, as it sparked a wider conversation about the statue's cultural significance and the need for greater understanding and respect for different perspectives."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue has been vandalized multiple times since its installation in 1913, with various incidents of general vandalism, including the aforementioned decapitation, explosive damage, and painting or graffiti, which have all contributed to the statue's complex and often tumultuous history."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The repeated intentional damages to the Little Mermaid statue have raised important questions about the role of public art in urban spaces, the impact of vandalism on cultural heritage, and the need for effective security measures to protect iconic landmarks like the Little Mermaid statue."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"As a cultural icon, the Little Mermaid statue has become a symbol of Copenhagen's rich history and cultural heritage, and its repeated vandalism has sparked a wider conversation about the importance of preserving and protecting public art for future generations."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The story of the Little Mermaid statue's repeated intentional damages serves as a reminder of the complex and often contentious nature of public art, and the need for ongoing efforts to protect and preserve cultural heritage in urban spaces."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"In the context of Copenhagen's cultural landscape, the Little Mermaid statue's history of vandalism highlights the importance of promoting greater understanding and respect for different perspectives, and the need for effective strategies to prevent future incidents of intentional damage."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue's story is a complex and multifaceted one, reflecting the broader social, cultural, and political currents that have shaped Copenhagen's urban landscape over the years, and its repeated vandalism serves as a reminder of the ongoing challenges of preserving and protecting public art in urban spaces."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"As a symbol of Copenhagen's cultural heritage, the Little Mermaid statue's history of vandalism underscores the importance of promoting greater awareness and appreciation for the city's rich cultural landscape, and the need for ongoing efforts to protect and preserve its iconic landmarks for future generations."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The repeated intentional damages to the Little Mermaid statue have signifi