es, causing significant damage."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The explosive damage in 2003 was not an isolated incident, as the statue was also damaged by an explosion in the same year, further emphasizing the need for increased security measures to prevent such incidents."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue has also been targeted with painting and graffiti, with a recent incident occurring in March 2023, when the Russian flag was painted on the stone it sits on, prompting a police investigation."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"In 2017, the statue was doused in red paint as part of a protest against whale hunting, demonstrating how the statue has become a focal point for various social and political movements."},{"citations":{"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":100.0},"text":"The statue was also defaced with graffiti reading 'racist fish' in 2020, during worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, highlighting the complex and often controversial nature of the statue's symbolism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The incident of painting the Russian flag on the base of the Little Mermaid statue in 2023 was not an isolated event, as unidentified individuals had also painted the same flag on the base, prompting a police investigation and raising concerns about the statue's security."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The defacing of the Little Mermaid statue with graffiti reading 'racist fish' in 2020 was a significant incident, as it sparked a wider conversation about the statue's cultural significance and the need for greater understanding and respect for different perspectives."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":100.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue has been 