391-260405"},"created":"2021-11-25T06:35:23.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1059","request_id":"1059","narrative_id":"1059"},"responses":[{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"Vertical gardens, also known as green walls, are increasingly integrated into urban environments to balance development with conservation by introducing green spaces into densely built areas."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"These installations offer significant environmental benefits, such as improving air quality by reducing nitrogen dioxide concentrations by 40%, particulate matter (PM10) by 60%, fine particulate matter (PM2.5) by 10%, and ozone (O3) by 30%."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"In Taichung City, green walls have been implemented in schools to enhance indoor air quality, retain dust, and absorb air pollution, creating healthier and more peaceful learning environments."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Beyond air purification, green walls contribute to temperature regulation by cooling building surfaces and reducing surrounding temperatures, which aids in energy conservation and carbon reduction."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"For instance, rooftop gardens can lower a building's surface temperature by 6 degrees Celsius and the ambient temperature by 4 degrees Celsius, demonstrating their role in mitigating urban heat islands."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"The mental health benefits of vertical gardens are also notable, as they create calming environments that promote well-being, as seen in their use in educational settings in Taichung."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"To ensure the success of vertical gardens, plant selection is critical, with species like Dragon Tubeh, Junzi, Wu Bamboo, and Honeysuckle being cost-effective and requiring minimal maintenance."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"In regions with extreme climates, introducing heat-resistant plants can improve the resilience of green walls, as demonstrated by annual reviews and horticultural adjustments in urban projects."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"Overall, vertical gardens represent a sustainable innovation in architecture, offering aesthetic appeal, environmental benefits, and improved quality of life while requiring thoughtful maintenance and plant selection."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"Vertical gardens, also known as green walls, are increasingly integrated into urban environments to balance development with conservation by introducing green spaces into densely built areas."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"These installations offer significant environmental benefits, such as improving air quality by reducing nitrogen dioxide concentrations by 40%, particulate matter (PM10) by 60%, fine particulate matter (PM2.5) by 10%, and ozone (O3) by 30%."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"In Taichung City, green walls have been implemented in schools to enhance indoor air quality, retain dust, and absorb air pollution, creating healthier and more peaceful learning environments."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Beyond air purification, green walls contribute to temperature regulation by cooling building surfaces and reducing surrounding temperatures, which aids in energy conservation and carbon reduction."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"For instance, rooftop gardens can lower a building's surface temperature by 6 degrees Celsius and the ambient temperature by 4 degrees Celsius, demonstrating their role in mitigating urban heat islands."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"The mental health benefits of vertical gardens are also notable, as they create calming environments that promote well-being, as seen in their use in educational settings in Taichung."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"To ensure the success of vertical gardens, plant selection is critical, with species like Dragon Tubeh, Junzi, Wu Bamboo, and Honeysuckle being cost-effective and requiring minimal maintenance."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"In regions with extreme climates, introducing heat-resistant plants can improve the resilience of green walls, as demonstrated by annual reviews and horticultural adjustments in urban projects."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"Overall, vertical gardens represent a sustainable innovation in architecture, offering aesthetic appeal, environmental benefits, and improved quality of life while requiring thoughtful maintenance and plant selection."}],"references":["ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194","a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749"],"documents":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":{"id":"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194","text":"More construction owners apply for subsidies to increase the garden high-rise green space area doubled in 10 years\nFont Size:\nOur high-rise green space has increased significantly, more than doubling in size over the past 10 years, from 60 hectares in 2013 to 155 hectares.\nIn addition to more new builders incorporating high-rise green spaces or rooftop gardens into their blueprints, more and more owners of older buildings are applying to the National Park Service for subsidies to add or convert their roofs into green spaces.\nIn an interview with the Lianhe Zaobao, the senior director of the National Park Service's landscaping department, Sophie Ann, revealed that since 2009, about 300 projects have applied for grants for high-rise green spaces or vertical landscaping.\nOwners who receive the allowance must ensure that the green space of the tall building is maintained for at least five years.\nAccording to the Park Service, only five applicants no longer maintain green spaces for high-rise buildings due to financial or other factors.\nThe Park Service annually reviews whether the green spaces in tall buildings are still lush and provides horticultural advice when needed, such as introducing heat-resistant and heat-resistant landscape plants to replace poorly grown flowers and trees.\nThe Park Service would not disclose how much subsidy has been allocated so far, but stressed that the purpose of the subsidy is to encourage more owners to pay attention to the benefits of high-rise green space, in line with Singapore \u2019 s 2030 Green Plan, to implement the vision of 200 hectares of high-rise green space.\nIn fact, many builders choose to set up garden green space in tall buildings or rooftops, or plant vertical flowers and trees in the outer layer of the building, while greening the building environment of steel cement, it also saves energy costs for cooling indoor space.\nRooftop gardens can \"cool\" the surface of a building by 6 degrees Celsius and reduce the surrounding temperature by 4 degrees Celsius, Sufian said.\nIn addition, when the solar panel is placed on the roof, if green plants are also planted below it, the solar panel can be prevented from overheating and the charging efficiency can be improved.\nMore intensive planting of various plants along the roadside\nGreen buildings such as vertical greening are a topic of concern in recent years, and integrating green space and natural habitat in new towns and residential areas can be one of the compromise solutions to balance urban development and conservation, and offset the plundering and depletion of the natural environment by development projects.\nAbout 40 percent of Singapore's land area is covered by green vegetation, many of which are naturally formed forests in the past half century.\nAfter the urban development of the 1970s, many rural and agricultural land was cleared, and tropical tree species that are easier to reproduce and grow quickly were planted, and many sub-forests were scattered everywhere.\nOver the years, the Park Service has also grown more dense and numerous plants per hectare of road land than in the past.\nIn the past, most of the plants on both sides of the road were of the same species. \"This is not a wise move, because if a certain species of tree is infected, it will affect a lot of trees,\" said Mr Woo Chao-shing, Senior Director of Roads and Landscape of the Park Service.\nAs a result, over the years, more diverse species of shrubs and trees have been added to create a sense of stratification along roadsides or open spaces, attracting more butterflies and birds, etc. \u201cAnd this will improve the fragmentation of green spaces caused by urbanization, strengthen ecological cohesion, repair roads and increase the destruction of nature by building more houses. \u201d\n\"When cities develop, we have to compensate by planting more plants in the same area of green corridors, or by choosing plants that grow faster to get back to the lush feeling of the past as soon as possible,\" Hu said.\nTo this end, the Park Service launched the rewilding project three years ago, deliberately ignoring the green corridors of 24 locations, reducing the number of routine pruning of branches and weeds and creating a sense of overgrown grass.\n\"We deliberately allow nature to grow freely, increasing its biodiversity and saving manpower, as long as it does not block the entrance of drainage channels or obstruct the passage of pedestrians,\" Hu said.\nHowever, some residents are concerned about mosquito breeding, and \"we will consider it on a case-by-case basis before deciding whether to expand the area under the plan.\"\nLIKE Our official Facebook page for more information","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0010.json.gz:24689","uncompressed_offset":695572194,"url":"www.zaobao.com.sg/news/singapore/story20230411-1381589","warc_date":"2023-04-11T02:41:27.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314>","warc_url":"https://www.zaobao.com.sg/news/singapore/story20230411-1381589"},"created":"2023-04-11T03:51:11.000Z","lang":"eng"},"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":{"id":"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749","text":"In order to improve the environmental air quality and let children learn with peace of mind, the Taichung Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau has continued to build a clean air green wall in the school. This year, 12 schools in Jianping Elementary School, Juren Elementary School and Chongde Elementary School have received subsidies from the Environmental Protection Department.\nAccording to the Environmental Protection Bureau, through the installation of clean air green walls, indoor air quality can be improved. At present, space such as classroom corridors and flower stands outside the daughter wall in Taichung City can be planted, which can achieve the benefits of dust retention, air pollution absorption and temperature regulation.\nIn order to strengthen the protection of the school environment for children, the Taichung City Environmental Protection Bureau expanded the subsidy for the construction of a clean air green wall on the campus, and the current subsidy amount to 1.76 million yuan, with an area of 358 square meters.\nThe Environmental Protection Bureau stressed that currently selected plants that can purify the air and do not need to spend too much money and time to maintain include the Dragon Tubeh, the Junzi and Wu Bamboo, the Turtle, the Cannonflower or the Honeysuckle.\nHow good is the effect of clean air green wall?\nAccording to international research, vertical clean air green walls can reduce the concentration of nitrogen dioxide (NO2) and particulate matter (PM10) by about 40% and 60%. In addition, green walls can also reduce the concentration of fine particulate matter (PM2.5) in classrooms by about 10% and the concentration of ozone (O3) by about 30%.\nGreen wall is the most natural and energy efficient air purification facilities, no need to plug in electricity, self-circulation, to achieve the purpose of air purification, can be called the \"most environmentally friendly air purifier\".\nChen Hongyi, director of the Environmental Protection Bureau, said that in addition to blocking outdoor pollutants and improving indoor air, the air green wall can also adjust the temperature and drive energy conservation and carbon reduction. Next year, Taichung City is expected to expand the subsidy target, including community activity centers, public kindergartens and environmental night markets.\n# Green Wall # Air # Cleanliness # Campus # Environment","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2021-0034.json.gz:14270","uncompressed_offset":458215749,"url":"www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20211125003391-260405","warc_date":"2021-11-25T05:58:05.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1>","warc_url":"https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20211125003391-260405"},"created":"2021-11-25T06:35:23.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1060","request_id":"1060","narrative_id":"1060"},"responses":[{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"Vertical gardens, also known as green walls, represent a significant innovation in sustainable architecture, blending environmental conservation with urban development by integrating green spaces into densely populated areas."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"These installations are increasingly recognized for their ability to enhance urban aesthetics while providing practical environmental benefits such as air purification, temperature regulation, and improved mental well-being."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"One notable example of vertical gardens in practice is the Taichung Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau's initiative, which introduced clean air green walls in schools to improve indoor air quality and foster a peaceful learning environment."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"These green walls, installed in areas like classroom corridors and flower stands, have demonstrated their capacity to retain dust, absorb air pollutants, and regulate indoor temperatures effectively."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Research has shown that vertical green walls can significantly reduce harmful air pollutants, including a 40% reduction in nitrogen dioxide (NO2), a 60% reduction in particulate matter (PM10), a 10% reduction in fine particulate matter (PM2.5), and a 30% reduction in ozone (O3)."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Unlike traditional air purification systems, green walls operate naturally and energy-efficiently, requiring no electricity while achieving self-circulation for air purification."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"In addition to improving air quality, vertical gardens contribute to temperature regulation by cooling building surfaces and reducing surrounding temperatures, which can lead to significant energy savings."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"For instance, rooftop gardens have been found to lower building surface temperatures by up to 6 degrees Celsius and reduce the ambient temperature by 4 degrees Celsius."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Green walls also play a role in adjusting indoor temperatures, thereby supporting energy conservation and reducing carbon emissions."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Beyond their environmental benefits, vertical gardens have a profound impact on mental health and well-being, as evidenced by their use in schools to create calming and conducive learning environments."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"The selection of plants for vertical gardens is critical to their success, with factors such as climate adaptability, maintenance requirements, and cost-effectiveness playing key roles."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"In Taichung, commonly used plants for green walls include Dragon Tubeh, Junzi, Wu Bamboo, Turtle, Cannonflower, and Honeysuckle, which are chosen for their resilience and minimal maintenance needs."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"To ensure the long-term viability of vertical gardens, regular maintenance is essential, including the periodic review of plant conditions and the introduction of heat-resistant species to replace underperforming vegetation."},{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"The integration of vertical gardens into urban architecture not only addresses environmental challenges but also enhances the aesthetic appeal of buildings, making them a valuable addition to sustainable design practices."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"ee5d394c-d8a3-4620-8ae0-47c7a481c314_695572194":100.0},"text":"Vertical gardens, also known as green walls, represent a significant innovation in sustainable architecture, blending environmental conservation with urban development by integrating green spaces into densely populated areas."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"These installations are increasingly recognized for their ability to enhance urban aesthetics while providing practical environmental benefits such as air purification, temperature regulation, and improved mental well-being."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"One notable example of vertical gardens in practice is the Taichung Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau's initiative, which introduced clean air green walls in schools to improve indoor air quality and foster a peaceful learning environment."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"These green walls, installed in areas like classroom corridors and flower stands, have demonstrated their capacity to retain dust, absorb air pollutants, and regulate indoor temperatures effectively."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Research has shown that vertical green walls can significantly reduce harmful air pollutants, including a 40% reduction in nitrogen dioxide (NO2), a 60% reduction in particulate matter (PM10), a 10% reduction in fine particulate matter (PM2.5), and a 30% reduction in ozone (O3)."},{"citations":{"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":100.0},"text":"Unlike traditional air purification systems, green walls operate naturally and energy-efficiently, requiring no electricity while achieving self-circulation for air purificatio