involves eliminating money-printing and pursuing a unified exchange rate to combat inflation and restore economic confidence."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279":100.0},"text":"As part of his economic restructuring efforts, Milei devalued the peso by approximately 50%, a move that has drawn both praise and criticism."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279":100.0},"text":"His administration has also issued decrees to repeal or amend hundreds of laws, aiming to curtail the power of trade unions and deregulate state interference in the economy."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279":100.0},"text":"Milei's broader reform plan includes privatizing state-owned entities and weakening labor protections, though these measures have faced resistance and legislative setbacks."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279":100.0},"text":"While his economic measures have boosted market confidence, they have also triggered nationwide protests and strong opposition from labor unions, who argue that the reforms disproportionately harm the poor."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Milei has proposed privatizing 41 state-owned companies across sectors such as energy, aviation, port administration, and agriculture as part of his broader neoliberal agenda."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"To facilitate these privatizations, his administration issued an 83-page Necessity and Urgency Decree (NDU) aimed at repealing over 300 laws and regulations."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Milei's omnibus bill, titled 'Foundations and Starting Points for the Freedom of the Argentine People,' bundles major neoliberal reforms into a single legislative package with 664 articles."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"The proposed dollarization of Argentina's economy, a key component of Milei's monetary policy, aims to combat hyperinflation by replacing the peso with the US dollar."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"However, dollarization would require congressional approval and potentially constitutional changes, making its implementation a complex and contentious process."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"Economists have raised concerns that adopting the US dollar could weaken Argentina's ability to manage its domestic monetary policy and increase vulnerability to external shocks."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"The estimated cost of dollarization, ranging from $35 billion to $50 billion, poses a significant financial challenge given Argentina's current economic constraints."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"Milei's political party, Libertad Avanza, holds only a minority in Congress, which has forced him to rely on executive powers to implement his reforms."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"This political isolation, coupled with a fragmented coalition, has posed significant challenges to advancing his legislative agenda."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"The defeat of a sprawling omnibus bill underscores the obstacles Milei faces from entrenched political factions and competing interests within Congress."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Milei's governing coalition holds only a fraction of the seats in Congress, leading him to adopt a strategy of bypassing legislative processes through emergency decrees."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"The omnibus bill includes provisions declaring a state of public emergency and delegating extraordinary powers to the executive until December 31, 2025, with a possible two-year extension."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Opposition politicians have made over 100 changes to the omnibus bill, including limiting emergency powers to one year and retaining YPF, the national oil and gas company, in public hands."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"Milei's reforms have faced fierce resistance from the left-leaning Peronist movement and powerful trade unions, which have historically dominated Argentine politics."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"Protests against his policies have included violent clashes with police, reflecting deep societal and political polarization."},{"citations":{"8d202821-55f3-4596-a337-a7b6e800f452_1024320475":100.0},"text":"Critics have accused Milei of undermining the spirit of the Constitution by bypassing Congress and governing through emergency decrees."},{"citations":{"6370ff20-0aef-4c5f-9655-68810eca5ff3_778249682":100.0},"text":"His austerity measures, including cuts to social subsidies and community kitchens, have exacerbated poverty and food insecurity, with 57% of the population now living in poverty."},{"citations":{"474c6eec-ebe5-4196-bca0-46e92bb6f014_959262116":100.0},"text":"Labor unions, which represent approximately 40% of Argentina's workforce, have announced nationwide strikes to protest Milei's rollback of worker protections and deregulation of industries."},{"citations":{"6370ff20-0aef-4c5f-9655-68810eca5ff3_778249682":100.0},"text":"Milei's administration has also repealed the law regulating the rental market, removing tenant protections and enabling landlords to terminate contracts at will."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"On the international stage, Milei has signaled alignment with the United States and Israel while initially suggesting a freeze in relations with Brazil and China."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"However, his foreign minister has dismissed concerns about rupturing commercial relations with China or Brazil, which are Argentina's top trading partners."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Milei's governance style, described as 'instant democracy,' prioritizes speed and flexibility in legislative processes to implement market-oriented reforms."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"This approach aligns with a global trend of 'neoliberal populism,' which rationalizes the concentration of executive power and the erosion of democratic standards."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"Milei has declared himself a climate change skeptic, denying the role of humans in global warming and proposing the elimination of the environment ministry."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"His stance on climate change risks isolating Argentina from the international community, particularly at global forums like the COP28 climate conference."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Environmental reforms in his omnibus bill include weakening the Glacier Protection Law to allow mining in sensitive areas, a move that has drawn criticism from environmentalists."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Javier Milei, who assumed the presidency of Argentina in December 2023, has embarked on a transformative policy agenda aimed at addressing the country's entrenched economic and institutional challenges."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"Central to Milei's economic reforms is his commitment to slashing state spending and achieving a budget surplus, a response to decades of fiscal mismanagement in Argentina."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"His administration has introduced a sweeping neoliberal restructuring program targeting nearly every aspect of government operations."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"One of the key legislative victories for Milei's libertarian agenda was the Senate's approval of state overhaul and tax bills, which marked an initial step in his broader reform strategy."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"The overhaul bill grants the president broad powers in areas such as energy, pensions, and security, while also including measures to privatize state-owned firms and incentivize foreign investment."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"Milei's tax reform package, which lowers the income tax threshold and offers a tax amnesty for undeclared assets, has sparked significant public backlash."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"In his first 100 days in office, Milei has pursued bold fiscal maneuvers and policy shifts, underscoring his commitment to economic reform."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"A cornerstone of his economic vision involves eliminating money-printing and pursuing a unified exchange rate to combat inflation and restore economic confidence."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279":100.0},"text":"As part of his economic restructuring efforts, Milei devalued the peso by approximately 50%, a move that has drawn both praise and criticism."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279":100.0},"text":"His administration has also issued decrees to repeal or amend hundreds of laws, aiming to curtail the power of trade unions and deregulate state interference in the economy."},{"citations":{"262765a4-72f4-4475-