rnal shocks."},{"citations":{"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091":100.0},"text":"The estimated cost of dollarization, ranging from $35 billion to $50 billion, poses a significant financial challenge given Argentina's current economic constraints."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"Milei's political party, Libertad Avanza, holds only a minority in Congress, which has forced him to rely on executive powers to implement his reforms."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"This political isolation, coupled with a fragmented coalition, has posed significant challenges to advancing his legislative agenda."},{"citations":{"42be5d07-d89d-4122-acf5-333f49984d59_948388057":100.0},"text":"The defeat of a sprawling omnibus bill underscores the obstacles Milei faces from entrenched political factions and competing interests within Congress."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Milei's governing coalition holds only a fraction of the seats in Congress, leading him to adopt a strategy of bypassing legislative processes through emergency decrees."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"The omnibus bill includes provisions declaring a state of public emergency and delegating extraordinary powers to the executive until December 31, 2025, with a possible two-year extension."},{"citations":{"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986":100.0},"text":"Opposition politicians have made over 100 changes to the omnibus bill, including limiting emergency powers to one year and retaining YPF, the national oil and gas company, in public hands."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677":100.0},"text":"Milei's reforms have faced fierce resistance from the left-leaning Peronist movement and powerful trade unions, which have historically dominated Argentine politics."},{"citations":{"9fc4b03d-d2ab-