& Shoots program, founded in 1991 in Tanzania, was created to address the loss of hope among young people due to climate change and biodiversity loss."},{"citations":{"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183":100.0},"text":"The program empowers young people to take action on projects that benefit animals, people, and the environment, emphasizing the interconnectedness of these elements."},{"citations":{"47120e3f-95ae-4a83-9c70-69d4b9024a90_952519686":100.0},"text":"Roots & Shoots has grown to include more than 8,000 sub-groups in approximately 140 countries, showcasing its global reach and influence."},{"citations":{"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183":100.0},"text":"Goodall aspires for the Roots & Shoots program to be implemented in every school worldwide to inspire collective action for conservation."},{"citations":{"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871":100.0},"text":"The program emphasizes that every individual has a role to play in helping the environment, people, and animals, as all are interrelated."},{"citations":{"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183":100.0},"text":"Goodall advocates for collaborative efforts between young and older generations to address environmental issues and save endangered species."},{"citations":{"f684acbb-658a-47ca-aaad-05e0fb187180_520597399":100.0},"text":"The Jane Goodall Institute, founded in 1977, includes the Roots & Shoots program and educates young people in over 60 countries on environmental, conservation, and humanitarian issues."},{"citations":{"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183":100.0},"text":"Goodall emphasizes the importance of giving young people hope while addressing environmental challenges, encouraging them to take action to make a difference."},{"citations":{"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871":100.0},"text":"Roots & Shoots inspires young people to create change within their communities and is active in 70 countries."},{"citations":{"52064d01-41a6-465