{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T215","run_id":"gar","topic_id":"1088","request_id":"1088","narrative_id":"1088"},"responses":[{"citations":{"c5fd6de6-97dd-43fb-baa0-6904cb595ccd_129588984":100.0},"text":"The India\u2013Russia relationship under Prime Minister Narendra Modi and President Vladimir Putin has been characterized by a deepening of defense and military cooperation, reflecting the historical ties between the two nations."},{"citations":{"044d6992-b71e-49ad-b4a4-f97ae3632c54_505910902":100.0},"text":"India continues to rely heavily on Russian-origin military equipment, with approximately 60% of its defense arsenal sourced from Russia, including Sukhoi fighter jets, tanks, and naval assets."},{"citations":{"cb08222e-8166-40e9-ab19-23aeca3cb9e5_8213419":100.0},"text":"During the Modi-Putin era, India and Russia have renewed their framework for military-technical cooperation, ensuring collaboration in defense for the next decade."},{"citations":{"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163":100.0},"text":"A significant milestone in defense cooperation was the finalization of a Rs 5,000 crore deal for the production of over five lakh AK-203 rifles in India, aligning with the \u2018Make in India\u2019 initiative."},{"citations":{"044d6992-b71e-49ad-b4a4-f97ae3632c54_505910902":100.0},"text":"India has also procured advanced S-400 anti-aircraft missile systems from Russia, despite the risk of U.S. sanctions, to bolster its air defense capabilities."},{"citations":{"044d6992-b71e-49ad-b4a4-f97ae3632c54_505910902":100.0},"text":"The S-400 systems are being strategically deployed in border areas to counter threats from China, highlighting the intersection of India\u2019s defense strategy and its rivalry with Beijing."},{"citations":{"cb08222e-8166-40e9-ab19-23aeca3cb9e5_8213419":100.0},"text":"India and Russia have also discussed logistics support agreements to allow their militaries to use each other\u2019s bases for repair and replenishment, further enhancing operational interoperability."},{"citations":{"c5fd6de6-97dd-43fb-baa0-6904cb595ccd_129588984":100.0},"text":"The ongoing Russia-Ukraine conflict has posed challenges to India\u2019s defense supplies, causing delays in deliveries and raising concerns over payment mechanisms."},{"citations":{"c5fd6de6-97dd-43fb-baa0-6904cb595ccd_129588984":100.0},"text":"Despite these challenges, the Russian defense industry has demonstrated resilience, ensuring continued support to India\u2019s armed forces."},{"citations":{"cb08222e-8166-40e9-ab19-23aeca3cb9e5_8213419":100.0},"text":"Strategic dialogues and summits have been pivotal in maintaining the momentum of India\u2013Russia relations, with mechanisms like the annual summit meetings providing a platform for reviewing bilateral ties."},{"citations":{"cb08222e-8166-40e9-ab19-23aeca3cb9e5_8213419":100.0},"text":"The introduction of the \u20182+2\u2019 defense and foreign ministerial dialogue has further institutionalized high-level discussions, involving key ministers from both sides to address strategic issues."},{"citations":{"cb08222e-8166-40e9-ab19-23aeca3cb9e5_8213419":100.0},"text":"The 21st India\u2013Russia summit, held in December 2021, underscored the commitment of both nations to expand cooperation in defense, trade, and energy."},{"citations":{"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430":100.0},"text":"However, the absence of leadership summits in recent years, partly due to Russia\u2019s preoccupation with the Ukraine conflict, has created a political gap that India has sought to address through ministerial visits."},{"citations":{"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430":100.0},"text":"Economic and trade relations between India and Russia have also seen significant growth, with bilateral trade exceeding $50 billion in recent years, driven by energy, fertilizers, and coking coal."},{"citations":{"e4c43534-8cf1-43c0-a42b-eb87a81fa36b_868308520":100.0},"text":"India has emerged as a major buyer of Russian oil, leveraging discounted prices to secure its energy needs amidst global volatility."},{"citations":{"a8edad1b-d157-466a-9ba5-057e6b4399d9_841501382":100.0},"text":"Despite this growth, a significant trade imbalance persists, with India importing about $60 billion worth of goods annually from Russia while exporting far less in return."},{"citations":{"792e3539-8d3e-404d-925f-2d2e14af8105_958547503":100.0},"text":"To address this imbalance, India and Russia have signed agreements to boost trade and joint investment projects, particularly in Russia\u2019s resource-rich Far East region."},{"citations":{"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430":100.0},"text":"Connectivity projects such as the International North-South Transport Corridor (INSTC) and the Chennai-Vladivostok route are critical components of their economic strategy, aimed at enhancing trade linkages."},{"citations":{"792e3539-8d3e-404d-925f-2d2e14af8105_958547503":100.0},"text":"These connectivity initiatives are designed to be free from political agendas, contrasting with China\u2019s Belt and Road Initiative, and emphasize transparency and respect for sovereignty."},{"citations":{"792e3539-8d3e-404d-925f-2d2e14af8105_958547503":100.0},"text":"The Northern Sea Route (NSR) is another key project, promising significant cost savings and reduced shipping times for goods traveling between Europe and Asia."},{"citations":{"792e3539-8d3e-404d-925f-2d2e14af8105_958547503":100.0},"text":"India and Russia have also discussed building a \u2018Greater Eurasian space\u2019 as a new architecture for cooperation in the Asia-Pacific region."},{"citations":{"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163":100.0},"text":"Amidst global geopolitical shifts, India has sought to balance its traditional ties with Russia while diversifying its partnerships, particularly with the United States."},{"citations":{"a8edad1b-d157-466a-9ba5-057e6b4399d9_841501382":100.0},"text":"Russia\u2019s growing alignment with Chin